2026-05-03 | Count Good Numbers After Rotation

	Question
Return count of good numbers from 1 to n.
	Key Insight
A number is GOOD if:
- contains only valid digits  
- contains at least one “changing digit”:
		2, 5, 6, 9  
	Approach (Simple Iteration)
1.	Loop from 1 to n  
2.	For each number:
		check digits  
3.	Flags:
		valid = true  
		diff = false  
4.	For each digit:
		if invalid → break  
		if in {2,5,6,9} → diff = true  
5.	If valid AND diff → count++  
	Time Complexity
	O(n × digits)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool isGood(int num){
        bool diff = false;
        while(num > 0){
            int d = num % 10;
            if(d == 3 || d == 4 || d == 7)
                return false;
            if(d == 2 || d == 5 || d == 6 || d == 9)
                diff = true;
            num /= 10;
        }
        return diff;
    }
    int rotatedDigits(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++){
            if(isGood(i))
                count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Two conditions must hold:
1.	No invalid digits  
2.	At least one digit changes after rotation  
This ensures:
		result is valid AND different  
This is a classic **digit classification problem**.
